message:
Initial commit:

- sets up test folder / run_tests script
- bootstrap
- module config files
- ready

Use pycodestyle instead of PEP8

PEP8 was renamed to pycodestyle; this issue explains why:
PyCQA/pycodestyle#466

This commit changes our tests to use pycodestyle instead of pep8.

No changes to our code were required as a result.

Remove Travis badge

We donâ€™t use Travis any more

Update email validation to reject commas in local part of address

- Also added a test to check that email addresses with a comma in the
domain part are not validated.
Fix a typo and formatting in README
Add link to the docs in main README

remove coverage from utils

we don't use it anywhere

Make README simpler

The README is overly verbose. I have stripped it down and removed the
bootstrap script that is doing so very little that I don't feel it adds
enough value anyway.

Remove section about virtualenv

This is covered generically in the Wiki [1].

[1]: https://github.com/alphagov/notifications-manuals/wiki/Getting-Started#development-environment

Remove broken link to nested README

This was removed in [1].

[1]: https://github.com/alphagov/notifications-utils/commit/332fe76d080738b5a2862c2371b81355e92a427f#diff-0b5ca119d2be595aa307d34512d9679e49186307ef94201e4b3dfa079aa89938

Standardise tasks in Makefile and README

This is consistent with our other repos.

add pre-commit hooks

remember to install them for this repo with
`pre-commit install --install-hooks`
